  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Remove the chicken from the fridge 30 mins before cooking to bring it to room temperature. Heat the oven to 190°C fan."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Grab a large roasting tray and drizzle enough olive oil to coat the base. Peel and quarter the onions, then place them face-down in the roasting tray."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pat the chicken dry with kitchen paper. Using your fingers, carefully lift the skin to create a space and rub the butter underneath. Stuff the cavity with ½ the lemon and the thyme. Season the skin generously with salt."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Place the chicken on a rack in the top half of the oven and slide the tray of onions into the shelf below (roasting the chicken on a rack lets the heat circulate around it, resulting in delicious rotisserie-style chicken, and the onions below will soak up all the juices). Roast for 1 hr 20 mins. Once cooked, remove from the oven and rest for 30 mins. Shred the meat with your hands."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "To make the Caesar dressing, add the mayonnaise, yoghurt, anchovies, garlic, Dijon mustard, and juice of the remaining lemon to a blender and blitz until smooth. Season with salt and black pepper."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Roughly chop the parsley. Put the kale into a large bowl with a pinch of salt and a drizzle of olive oil. Scrunch with your hands to soften, then toss in the parsley, shredded chicken, dressing and grated Parmesan."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Box it up and enjoy easy sandwiches all week with zero faff! It will keep in the fridge for 3 days. Sandwich the filling and roasted onions between slices of your favourite bread and you’re good to go."
    }
  ],
